-- Koza Anadolu Gains in Istanbul After Full-Year Profit Leaps
-- B y   A y d a n   E k s i n
-- 2012-04-12T15:25:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-12/koza-anadolu-gains-in-istanbul-after-full-year-profit-leaps-1-.html
Koza Anadolu Metal Madencilik
Isletmeleri AS (KOZAA) , a Turkish miner, climbed for a second day in
Istanbul after saying its full-year profit jumped.  Koza Anadolu rose 3.1 percent to 3.29 liras at the close in
Istanbul, the biggest rise since April 2.  Net income rose 83 percent to 174 million liras ($97
million) in 2011 from 95.2 million liras in the previous year,
the company said in a statement to the  Istanbul Stock Exchange 
today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
